radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar subsegmental atelectasis in the lung bases; multiple hypodensities in the liver likely representing cysts; diffuse ductal dilation of the pancreas; markedly enlarged uterus with multiple enhancing fibroids; mucosal thickening and hyperenhancement of the appendix with enlargement measuring 10 mm in diameter; small amount of focal periependymal fluid; no free gas or fluid in the upper abdomen; no pelvic sidewall or inguinal lymphadenopathy; no suspicious osseous lesions.
